Ayala, Metro Pacific, MRC Allied: Philippine Stocks Preview

-- B y   I a n   C .   S a y s o n
-- 
2011-05-24T00:50:57Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-05-24/ayala-metro-pacific-mrc-allied-philippine-stocks-preview.html
Shares of the following companies may
have unusual moves in Philippine trading. Stock symbols are in
parentheses, and prices are as of the previous close, unless
stated otherwise.  The Philippine Stock Exchange Index fell 0.5 percent to
4,263.19.  Ayala Corp. (AC)  : The owner of the largest Philippine
property builder bought back 27,500 shares, a stock-exchange
filing showed. The stock climbed 0.5 percent to 372 pesos.  Metro Pacific Tollways Corp. (TOL)  : The company said it
agreed to review in 60 days a contract awarded by Bases
Conversion and Development Authority for the company to manage
the Subic-Clark-Tarlac Expressway, a stock exchange filing
showed. The government wants the contract, awarded in November,
terminated, the filing showed. Metro Pacific Tollways was
unchanged at 7.50 pesos when it last traded on May 17.  Metro
Pacific Investments Corp. (MPI)  , owner of the tollroad
operator, fell 2.3 percent to 3.42 pesos.  MRC Allied Inc. (MRC)  : The Philippine company said it’s
“closer” to getting all the government permits to start
production at the Tampakan-Kiblawan Mines, a stock exchange
filing showed. The stock was unchanged at 72 centavos.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Ian C. Sayson in Manila at 
 isayson@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
